draw((-400,0)--(400,0));
draw((0,-200)--(0,200));

label("$y = f_0(x)$", (400,200), E);
label("$(-100,100)$", (-100,100), N);
label("$(100,-100)$", (100,-100), S);
[/asy]

Thus, the equation $f_0(x) = \pm 100$ has two solutions, and the equation $f_0(x) = 2k$ has three solutions for $-49 \le k \le 49.$  Thus, the number of solutions to $f_{100}(x) = 0$ is $2 + 2 + 3 \cdot 99 = 301.$

