The intersection of lines $y = 2x + 2$ and $y = \frac{1}{2} x + 1$ is $\left( -\frac{2}{3}, \frac{2}{3} \right),$ and the intersection of lines $y = \frac{1}{2} x + 1$ and $y = -\frac{3}{4} x + 7$ is $\left( \frac{24}{5}, \frac{17}{5} \right).$

We can show that $f(x)$ is increasing on the interval $\left( -\infty, \frac{24}{5} \right],$ and decreasing on the interval $\left[ \frac{24}{5}, \infty \right).$  Thus, the maximum value of $f(x)$ is $f \left( \frac{24}{5} \right) = \frac{17}{5}.$
